  "body": "<!-- Have you done the following? -->\r\n<!--   * read the Code of Conduct? By filing an Issue, you are expected to -->  \r\n<!--     comply with it, including treating everyone with respect: -->\r\n<!--     https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/blob/master/CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md -->\r\n<!--   * Reproduced the issue in the latest version of the software -->\r\n<!--   * Read the debugging wiki: https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/wiki/debugging -->\r\n<!--   * Duplicate Issue check:  https://github.com/search?q=+is%3Aissue+repo%3Ahyperledger/Besu -->\r\n<!-- Note:  Not all sections will apply to all issue types. -->\r\n\r\n### Description\r\nWithout `rpc-http-host=[\"0.0.0.0\"]`, the RPC node rejects calls from dapp. In my case the dapp was just waiting and waiting. A error message from RPC node will help developer/user to quickly identify the problem. Also in situation of in sufficient validator, no message is sent from RPC nodes as well.\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* [Criteria 1]\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\r\n1. Use config.toml without whitelist for rpc-http-host.\r\n2. [Step 2]. Deploy a contract from etherjs (`contract.deployTransaction`). Web3 may do as well\r\n3. [Step ...]. Check the console log to see if there is any message returned. There shouldn't be any.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** [What you expect to happen]\r\nSend out error message when RPC node rejects a call because the host is not on whitelist.\r\n**Actual behavior:** [What actually happens]\r\nNo any message sent\r\n**Frequency:** [What percentage of the time does it occur?]\r\nalways\r\n### Versions (Add all that apply)\r\n* Software version: [`besu --version`]:1.5.0/20.10.2. IBFT2\r\n* Java version: [`java -version`]:15\r\n* OS Name & Version: [`cat /etc/*release`] Win10\r\n* Kernel Version: [`uname -a`]\r\n* Virtual Machine software & version: [`vmware -v`]\r\n* Docker Version: [`docker version`]\r\n* Cloud VM, type, size: [Amazon Web Services I3-large]\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n",
